procedures.name: Blood Sampling

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation, pregnancy, and viral screening tests.

procedures.name: Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of urine samples for urinalysis, drug screening, pregnancy testing, and measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: 24-hour Urine Collection

code.decode: Volume measurement for timed collection, each

procedures.label: 24-hour Urine Collection
procedures.description: Collection of all urine over a 24-hour period for measurement of copper and molybdenum.

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Fecal Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of fecal samples for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A full or symptom-driven physical examination, including assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate, intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc), and other clinically significant findings.

procedures.name: Height, Weight, and BMI Measurement
procedures.label: Anthropometric Measurements
procedures.description: Measurement of height, weight, and calculation of Body Mass Index (BMI).

procedures.name: Urinalysis

code.decode: Urinalysis, by dip stick or tablet reagent for bilirubin, glucose, hemoglobin, ketones, leukocytes, nitrite, pH, protein, specific gravity, urobilinogen, any number of these constituents; automated, with microscopy

procedures.label: Urinalysis
procedures.description: Laboratory assessment of urine for safety monitoring.

procedures.name: Urine Drug Screen
procedures.label: Urine Drug Screen
procedures.description: Screening for disallowed drugs via a urine sample.

procedures.name: Pregnancy Test
procedures.label: Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Urine and/or serum pregnancy tests for females of childbearing potential.

procedures.name: Adverse Event Monitoring
procedures.label: AE Monitoring
procedures.description: Collection and follow-up of adverse events (AEs) and serious adverse events (SAEs).

procedures.name: Bowel and Urine Output Monitoring
procedures.label: Intake/Output Monitoring
procedures.description: Monitoring and recording of all urination and bowel movements for balance assessments.

procedures.name: Food and Fluid Sample Collection
procedures.label: Dietary Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of samples from all meal and fluid batches for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms for cardiac safety monitoring.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure Device
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Monitor
medicalDevices.description: A completely automated device for assessing blood pressure and heart rate.

medicalDevices.name: Intravenous Cannula
medicalDevices.label: IV Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula may be placed to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively Coupled Plasma Mass Spectrometry Analyzer
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS Analyzer
medicalDevices.description: Laboratory equipment used to determine the copper and molybdenum concentration of food, fluid, urine, and fecal samples.
